dcterms:description: The OntoNotes 5.0 corpus is the largest available NER corpus for English, comprising multi-genre text with linguistic annotations covering multiple layers such as part of speech, parse structure, co-reference, proposition, word sense, and named entity recognition (NER). It consists of 3,637 documents and 2 million tokens, annotated with 18 named entity types.
dcterms:title: OntoNotes 5.0

dcterms:creator: E. T. K. Sang
F. De Meulder
dcterms:description: The CONLL-03 dataset is a well-known dataset for language-independent named entity recognition, used in the CoNLL-2003 shared task. It provides annotated data for training and evaluating NER systems.
dcterms:title: CONLL-03
